      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### Key motifs / functional groups\n- **Fused bicyclic heteroaromatic system**: a **benzimidazole-like**/aza-fused bicyclic core with a **[nH]** (one ring N is protonatable only weakly; largely neutral at pH 7.4).\n- **Tertiary amide**: `N(C(=O)Ar)\u2026` where the amide nitrogen is part of a side chain. **Amide N is not basic** (strongly resonance-stabilized).\n- **Secondary amide**: `NC(=O)\u2026` (also **not basic**).\n- **Multiple aromatic/hydrophobic domains**:\n  - One **fused bicyclic aromatic** system\n  - An additional **phenyl** attached to the tertiary amide N\n  - A **para-anilide** ring\n  - A **biaryl (biphenyl)** group on the terminal amide (very lipophilic, bulky)",
      "tool_name": null,
